==English==
===Verb===
'''garnish''' (garnishes, garnished, garnishing)
# To decorate with ornamental appendages; to set off; to adorn; to embellish.
# All within with flowers was garnished.
# (Cookery) To ornament, as a dish, with something laid about it; as, a dish garnished with parsley.
# To furnish; to supply.
# To fit with fetters.
# (Law) To warn by garnishment; to give notice to; to garnishee. Se
